<theme id="thm221">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Tied dotted 8th note</title>
<tocimage>img221.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson the next patterns are introduced:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4 noVisible)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. g-)(barline double)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. l g-)(n * q)(barline double)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. l g-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. g-)(n * s g+)(n * e. g-)(barline)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. l g-)(n * q)(barline)
        (n * s g+)(n * e. l g-)(n * e g+)(n * e g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm221_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear: Pattern of 16th note and 
dotted 8th note.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm221_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Train your ear: 16th note and dotted 8th
note tied to quarter note.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm221_E3">Exercise 3</link> - Train your ear: 16th note and dotted 8th 
note tied to 8th note.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm221_E4">Exercise 4</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

